* Iron Raptor snapped her head towards Dark One as he laughed at her, the look of white hot rage in her optics. But then she sighed and looked back at Nemesis, hearing just how the buge worked.
She shook her head and pressed even harder against the wall, her optics wide but then narrowed. There was no chance in Hell they were going to get that thing on her neck...not without loosing a hand or two!
But then Iron Raptor looked at the wicked poll Nemesis gestured to and decided that she would chose that over the bug if she had a choice, but she didn't and that was what scared her now. That her own mind might be so warped by the pain this bug caused...that there would be nothing left of her sanity when they finished.
She watched one of the bugs switch hands to Dark One, watching every one of his moves as Nemesis told him to charge it.
Iron Raptor looked back at Tavatron, worry now plainly written in her optics now that she knew that help wasn't coming.
Prowl wasn't there, he wasn't there.
That was all she could think about as Dark One charged the bug, about just how the one she always thought would be with her and the one to protect her was now nowhere to be seen.
Her spark sank but she didn't let them know, keeping the blank look on her face as she hung her head.*
